# Review Changes Skill

## Pre-flight

Run before reading diffs:

- `git status` — what's staged vs unstaged
- `git diff --staged` and `git diff` — see all changes
- `yarn tsc --noEmit` — type clean?
- `yarn lint` — lint clean?
- `yarn check` — Prettier clean?
- `yarn test` — green?

If any of these fail, fix first; review starts from a clean baseline.

## Checklist (block on red)

- [ ] Every new exported function / hook / component has explicit input and output types.
- [ ] No `any`, no non-null `!`, no default exports outside framework-required spots (TanStack Router file-based routes use `export const Route`).
- [ ] No magic numbers / strings — meaningful literals live in a `constants.ts` or alongside their schema.
- [ ] Layer boundaries respected: `lib/` doesn't import from `routes/`, `components/`, or `hooks/`; `components/ui/*` doesn't import from feature components.
- [ ] Type-only imports use `import type { … }` (verbatimModuleSyntax is on).
- [ ] Path aliases consistent in each file (don't mix `#/` and `@/`).
- [ ] Class names merged with `cn()` — no manual string concatenation of Tailwind classes.
- [ ] Token utilities preferred over arbitrary hex (use `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, brand `var(--…)` over `#173a40`).
- [ ] External boundary inputs validated with Zod (form submits, server-function payloads, search-params).
- [ ] No floating promises. No swallowed errors. Catch payloads typed as `unknown` and narrowed.
- [ ] `src/routeTree.gen.ts` not edited by hand.
- [ ] Route paths referenced via the typed `<Link to=...>` / `useNavigate()` API, not retyped strings.
- [ ] No new dependency added without justification (and the version is a real released version, not invented).
- [ ] Tests cover the change (happy path + ≥ 1 edge case) when the change has logic worth testing.

## Output format

For each finding:

- 🔴 Critical — must fix before merge (anything in the checklist above)
- 🟡 Suggestion — would improve clarity, performance, or symmetry with existing code
- 🟢 Nit — optional polish

Each finding cites: file path, line(s), the problem, the suggested fix.

## Verify before reporting

- `yarn tsc --noEmit` clean
- `yarn lint` clean
- `yarn check` clean
- Touched files only — don't expand scope.
